Free is when you kill the mob with your guild all doing their jobs, the way bards got their white scales before Manaburn Wandor<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes I am pretty familiar with the free concept and what Brik meant by that. My point is that the majority of bards, and for that matter warriors, end up purchasing their scales. It has been like this since long before there was a mana burn. That's why scales where so expensive and rare.<br>
<br>
Now you and I both know that PoP is not the only reason MB was nerfed. It would have been a lot easier to flag PoP mobs non-burnable, but VI had to address the people who where complaining (right or wrong is irrelevent) about MB teams. Read the post about it, it specifically addresses MB teams &quot;holding epics hostage&quot;. VI at least had the sense to state that they knew it was a small group of people doing this.<br>
<br>
Regardless of what your opinion is on MB, the fact of the matter is that on the majority of servers, even those where there was an actual problem with greedy loot farmers, the prices of epic pieces and other dragon loot dropped. what may have been considered a detriment to some, was a boon to others (who could not kill dragons).<br>
<br>
Not that any of this matters, MB was nerfed and small groups of wizards are still killing dragons (9 killed Sev today with no deaths or support people). Sooner or later everyone will have to come to the realization that 32k mobs from 3 expansions ago are going to be trivial to top level players with current equipment, spells, and skills. Just wait until 6 level 65 wizards nuke Gore down with Stike of Solusek (2740 fire DD), what will people think then? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uskipylz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skipy LZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/17/02 3:01:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1790.topic&index=209>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   re</span><hr size=1> FYI, MB team got severilous toonight with 9 people. They ll soon be able to make it again with 5 wiz and 1 puller<br>
